exercises.name: Bench Press
exercises.description: A chest exercise that involves pressing a barbell from chest level to arm's length.

exercises.name: Pull Up
exercises.description: An upper body exercise where you pull yourself up on a bar until your chin is above it.

exercises.name: Deadlift
exercises.description: A compound exercise that involves lifting a barbell from the ground to hip level.

exercises.name: Squat
exercises.description: A lower body exercise where you bend your knees and lower your hips as if sitting back into a chair.

exercises.name: Plank
exercises.description: A core strength exercise where you hold a push-up position with your body straight and supported on your elbows and toes.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Curl
exercises.description: An arm exercise where you curl dumbbells from a straight arm position to shoulder level.

exercises.name: Tricep Dips
exercises.description: An exercise that targets the triceps by lowering and raising your body using parallel bars.

exercises.name: Leg Press
exercises.description: A lower body exercise performed on a leg press machine to push weights away from your body with your legs.

exercises.name: Lat Pulldown
exercises.description: A machine exercise where you pull a weighted bar down towards your chest, targeting the lats.

exercises.name: Shoulder Press
exercises.description: An overhead pressing movement targeting the shoulders, triceps, and upper chest.
